## Current Relay URL Configuration

**Location:** `/Users/zvada/conductor/workspaces/deus-machine/manama-v2/apps/backend/src/services/relay.service.ts`

**Current Implementation (lines 103-108):**

```typescript
export function ensureRelayConnected(): void {
  let url = getSetting("relay_url") as string | null;
  if (!url) {
    url = DEFAULT_RELAY_URL;
    saveSetting("relay_url", url);
  }
  // ... rest of function
}
```

**The Issue:** The code currently:
1. Reads `relay_url` from the settings database (line 104)
2. Only falls back to `DEFAULT_RELAY_URL` if the DB value is null/missing
3. Saves the default URL back to the DB if it was missing (line 107)

This means **if a user has an old/wrong relay_url stored in the DB, it will be used instead of the current DEFAULT_RELAY_URL** (which is defined in `lib/network.ts` as `"wss://relay.deusmachine.ai"`).

**The Fix Has NOT Been Applied Yet**. You need to change the logic to always use `DEFAULT_RELAY_URL` and ignore the DB value. The corrected code should be:

```typescript
export function ensureRelayConnected(): void {
  let url = DEFAULT_RELAY_URL;  // Always use the hardcoded default
  // ... rest of function (remove the getSetting/saveSetting logic)
}
```

Also note that line 160 in `getRelayStatus()` still reads from the DB as a fallback:
```typescript
const effectiveUrl = relayUrl ?? (getSetting("relay_url") as string | undefined) ?? null;
```

This should also be simplified to always use `DEFAULT_RELAY_URL`.

