## DialogOverlay Component Analysis

**File:** `/Users/zvada/conductor/workspaces/deus-machine/manama-v2/apps/web/src/components/ui/dialog.tsx`

### Current Implementation (Lines 23-39)

The `DialogOverlay` is defined as a **plain function** (not using `forwardRef`):

```tsx
function DialogOverlay({
  className,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<typeof DialogPrimitive.Overlay>) {
  return (
    <DialogPrimitive.Overlay
      data-slot="dialog-overlay"
      className={cn(
        "fixed inset-0 z-50 bg-black/50 will-change-[opacity]",
        "data-[state=open]:animate-[overlay-enter_200ms_cubic-bezier(.215,.61,.355,1)]",
        "data-[state=closed]:animate-[overlay-exit_150ms_cubic-bezier(.215,.61,.355,1)]",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}
```

### Key Observations

1. **No `forwardRef`** — The component does not use `React.forwardRef()`, which means it cannot accept or forward refs
2. **Props spread correctly** — The `{...props}` does get passed to `DialogPrimitive.Overlay`, so that part is good
3. **Missing ref handling** — Any `ref` passed to `DialogOverlay` will be silently ignored since there's no ref parameter in the function signature

### To Fix For Ref Support

To properly support refs, this would need to be wrapped with `forwardRef`:

```tsx
const DialogOverlay = React.forwardRef<
  React.ElementRef<typeof DialogPrimitive.Overlay>,
  React.ComponentProps<typeof DialogPrimitive.Overlay>
>(({ className, ...props }, ref) => (
  <DialogPrimitive.Overlay
    ref={ref}
    data-slot="dialog-overlay"
    className={cn(...)}
    {...props}
  />
));
DialogOverlay.displayName = "DialogOverlay";
```

